-- Russia May Decide on Grain Export Limits in Days, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-03-13T04:44:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/russia-may-decide-on-grain-export-limits-in-days-vedomosti-says.html
Russia  will not limit exports of
grain during the season ending June 30, and “official
information” is expected soon,  Vedomosti  said, citing
unidentified officials at trading houses and trade associations.  A statement on grain exports will be made in days,
Vedomosti said, citing Prime Minister Vladimir Putin’s
spokesman,  Dmitry Peskov , without elaborating. A final decision
hasn’t been made, the newspaper said, citing an unidentified
official in Deputy Prime Minister Viktor Zubkov’s office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
